<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>ReportDesk Import Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/import.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="main">
        <!-- Paste the navigation bar here -->
        <header>
            <nav>
                <a class="navbar-brand" href="https://www.untdallas.edu"><img src="/images/UNTDlogo.png" alt="UNTDlogo"></a>
                <a class="navbuttons" href="/users/getRecords">Records</a>
                <a class="navbuttons" href="/users/create-user">Users</a>
                <a class="navbuttons" href="/reports/getHeadcount">Count</a>
                <a class="navbuttons" href="/reports/getReportpage">Reports</a>
                <a class= "navbuttons"href="/users/logout">LogOut</a>
                <figure class="reportdesk">ReportDesk</figure>
                
            </nav>
        </header>
        <!-- End of navigation bar -->
      
        
        <section>
            <p>The current file types the system accepts at the moment are XML,CSV, and Excel. However, for XML they should be formatted in the following way. For XML, each entry should have an associated category. Underneath it should include any information that is known for that entry.
            <a href="/samples/XML_Example.xml" download><strong> Here </strong></a> is an example of how an XML file should look like.
            </p>
            <p>For either Excel or CSV files, they should be formatted in similar styles. The header of the file is the type of information that is being inserted, and each row containing information knows about that entry. 
            <a href="/samples/Excel_Example.xlsx" download><strong> Here </strong></a> an example of an Excel spreadsheet, and <a href="/samples/CSV_Example.csv" download><strong> here </strong></a>is an example of a CSV.
            </p>
            <p>Please upload your file</p>
            <form id="submit" action="/users/import" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                <input type="file" name="file" accept=".csv,.xml,.xlsx" /><br />
                <input type="submit" value="Upload" />
            </form>
        </section>
    </div>
    <% if (typeof error !== 'undefined') { %>
    <script> alert('<%= error %>'); window.location.href = '/users/import'; </script>
    <% } %>
    <% if (typeof message !== 'undefined') { %>
    <script> alert('<%= message %>'); window.location.href = '/users/import'; </script>
    <% } %>
</body>
</html>
